<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 2:24PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Scotland,
southeastern Richmond and south central Hoke Counties through 300 PM
EDT...
At 223 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hamlet, or 10 miles west of Laurinburg, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Hamlet, Maxton, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg, Laurel
Hill and Bowmore.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
